Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.49,0:00:14.24,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,What is it, Akatsuki?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.24,0:00:16.12,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,N-Nothing, just...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.63,0:00:18.94,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Aren't you going to the party, my lord?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.26,0:00:22.45,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,No, I don't care for those flashy events.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.10,0:00:24.71,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,I'll let Crusty handle it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.58,0:00:26.82,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.31,0:02:09.15,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I hear you did a fantastic job!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.15,0:02:12.36,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,I'm told you easily defeated the Goblin General.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.36,0:02:15.73,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,I believe that victory was only possible
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.73,0:02:19.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,because People of the Land and \Nadventurers worked together.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.15,0:02:21.99,Default - italics,L,0000,0000,0000,,Please. You don't really think that.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.22,0:02:24.13,Default,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,He's so strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.13,0:02:25.61,Default,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,He's wonderful!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.25,0:02:37.21,Title,S,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(1611,1)}The Two of Us Shall Waltz
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.61,0:02:35.15,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,The Two of Us Shall Waltz.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.19,0:02:40.48,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,The food here is great!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.48,0:02:45.16,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Shiroe and his buddies ate this stuff \Nevery day during the conferences?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.16,0:02:47.32,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,Wherever you eat it,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.32,0:02:51.88,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,the food you enjoy with friends \Nis the most delicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.88,0:02:53.83,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Where's the hide-and-seek genius?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.83,0:02:55.20,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Where is she?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.20,0:02:57.11,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't she here today?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.44,0:02:58.52,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.52,0:02:59.73,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,You aren't eating.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.19,0:03:02.62,Default,Sh,0000,0000,0000,,We haven't wiped out the goblins,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.04,0:03:05.06,Default,Sh,0000,0000,0000,,so how can we celebrate victory?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.57,0:03:10.00,Default,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,It's been a month since we pinned the \Ngoblin army on the Zantleaf Peninsula.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.51,0:03:15.59,Default,Sh,0000,0000,0000,,The Goblin King is still at their \Nheadquarters in Seventh Fall.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.46,0:03:18.96,Default,Sh,0000,0000,0000,,Why can't we go destroy him right now?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.96,0:03:23.28,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,It's more important to build our \Nrelationships with the People of the Land.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.28,0:03:26.21,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,That was Shiroe's decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.36,0:03:30.11,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,Over the past month,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.11,0:03:34.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the Round Table has signed basic \Ntrade and peace treaties
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.27,0:03:38.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,with Eastal's League of Freedom Cities.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.08,0:03:44.67,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,The Round Table has issued many goblin-fighting\Nquests to adventures in Akihabara,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.67,0:03:46.78,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,which has kept the goblins in Zantleaf.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.38,0:03:49.14,Default,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,Then this is
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.14,0:03:54.01,Default,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,reminding everyone that adventurers \Nare accepting quests again.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.60,0:03:57.22,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,And if we defeat their king first,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.22,0:04:00.50,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,the goblins will go out of control without a leader.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.50,0:04:04.93,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,All of this is part of Shiroe's plan \Nto take out Seventh Fall.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.93,0:04:06.04,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,I understand...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.36,0:04:09.17,Default,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,He's thinking several steps ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.46,0:04:12.43,Default,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,Are you certain?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.60,0:04:16.10,Default,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,I can really join Log Horizon?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.10,0:04:18.07,Default,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, that's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.36,0:04:20.04,Default,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,I'll let Shiro know.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.04,0:04:21.75,Default,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,Th-Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.75,0:04:25.07,Default,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,After all you've done, and \Nall the help you've given me...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.07,0:04:28.45,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Friends should stay together, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.93,0:04:33.04,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Leave Miss Isuzu to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.04,0:04:36.85,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,With the strength of the adventurer \NRundel Haus Code, Akihabara is—
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.85,0:04:39.59,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you! Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.10,0:04:43.41,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,I'm happy for Isuzu.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.10,0:04:48.22,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Shiroe?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.60,0:04:50.39,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Shiroe?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.39,0:04:51.94,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you looking there?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.94,0:04:53.60,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,Is something wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.95,0:04:56.12,Default,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, I haven't seen him.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.12,0:04:59.68,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Shiroe is the Akihabara army's strategist.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.68,0:05:02.57,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,He should be one of the guests of honor.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.57,0:05:05.53,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,But he isn't even here to say hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.53,0:05:06.95,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.95,0:05:09.49,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,That sounds like him.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.49,0:05:11.99,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Sounding like him doesn't excuse this behavior!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.99,0:05:12.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Meow...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.19,0:05:19.52,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,My lord...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.88,0:05:20.87,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.87,0:05:22.55,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Shiroe!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.94,0:05:23.76,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.05,0:05:27.48,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Akatsuki, take care of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.48,0:05:28.56,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,My lord!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.20,0:05:32.93,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Akatsuki!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.93,0:05:34.56,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Let's get you changed!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.56,0:05:36.71,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, do you know where Shiroe is?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.71,0:05:39.68,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, you smell so good!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.42,0:05:42.94,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Akatsuki?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.39,0:05:47.82,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,That was close.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.70,0:05:51.31,HUD Big,S,0000,0000,0000,,{\an7}Ooshima \N{\fs20}The Little Birdies
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.97,0:05:51.02,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Ooshima?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.72,0:05:53.01,Default,Guild,0000,0000,0000,,How's it going since then?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.74,0:05:55.49,Default,Guild,0000,0000,0000,,What? In the west?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.04,0:05:57.89,Default,Guild,0000,0000,0000,,The Demon Festival of Suzaku Gate?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.96,0:06:00.27,Default,Guild,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.27,0:06:01.55,Default,Guild,0000,0000,0000,,So that's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.84,0:06:07.11,Default,Guys,0000,0000,0000,,So we were just ripping up goblins, \Ntossing them aside...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.11,0:06:09.72,Default,Guys,0000,0000,0000,,You could hear the Phoenix's roar \Necho through the whole valley!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.91,0:06:11.23,Default,Guys,0000,0000,0000,,Boom!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.23,0:06:16.60,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,They don't know that they'll lose some \Nof their memories if they die.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.87,0:06:22.02,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,We've only told the Round Table's \Nmajor members about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.48,0:06:26.28,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,Well, knowing Shiro, I'm sure he'll handle it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.34,0:06:31.34,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,I'd love it if you'd visit my territory sometime.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.34,0:06:36.40,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,I'd love for you to tell my troops \Nsome tales of your victories!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.40,0:06:39.18,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,No, no, please visit me, as well!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.18,0:06:45.17,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,My daughter is seeking a husband, \Nand I think you'd get along well.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.00,0:06:51.34,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,Grandfather, is that...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.03,0:06:55.61,Default,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,And then? And then?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.61,0:06:56.99,Default,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.58,0:07:03.21,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,And then, heroes from a \Ndifferent world came to ours.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.12,0:07:10.11,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,They were immortal, strong, and wise.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.52,0:07:11.60,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,I know that!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.60,0:07:13.02,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,The Precursors, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.02,0:07:15.06,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,The Izumo Knights, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.06,0:07:20.69,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,No, they were far more \Npowerful than the Precursors.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.69,0:07:21.67,Default,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, my!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.03,0:07:26.21,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,One day, the king of monsters \Nappeared with his army,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.21,0:07:28.86,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,burning villages, destroying castles,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.86,0:07:31.68,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,and ruining fields.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.60,0:07:37.22,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,The heroes came quickly, and defeated \Nthe monsters, one after the next.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.65,0:07:42.32,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,The monsters that had covered the beaches, \Nthose that blackened the forest...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.52,0:07:46.66,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,But during the battle,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.66,0:07:50.03,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,one of them lost his life.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.87,0:07:53.54,Default,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,That's strange...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.54,0:07:55.66,Default,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,Weren't they immortal?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.12,0:08:01.04,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,The boy who died was merely one \Nof the People of the Land,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.04,0:08:04.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,one who longed to be one of those heroes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.82,0:08:05.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, my!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.20,0:08:11.74,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,The heroes begged their wizard to save him.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.74,0:08:14.17,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,But not even their wizard
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.17,0:08:17.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,knew how to restore one of \Nthe People of the Land.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.16,0:08:19.26,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,And then?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.26,0:08:20.72,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,What happened next?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.87,0:08:25.70,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,So the wizard thought, and then, of all things,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.70,0:08:31.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,he created a new form of magic \Nthat hadn't existed in this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.67,0:08:39.17,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,And so, the young boy of the \NPeople of the Land became a hero.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.95,0:08:44.61,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,But after that, the wizard...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.90,0:08:46.34,Default,All,0000,0000,0000,,What? What?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.18,0:08:48.77,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,That's all for today.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.77,0:08:51.11,Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,We'll continue the story next time.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.11,0:08:52.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aww!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.67,0:08:55.13,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,No, there's no way...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.37,0:09:02.67,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, hello there.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.67,0:09:04.77,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,I am honored by your visit.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.06,0:09:08.62,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,And congratulations, Shiroe.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.53,0:09:10.82,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,For what?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.52,0:09:14.05,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,The creation of a new type of magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.88,0:09:16.95,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,What? You noticed?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.31,0:09:18.65,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,A month ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.65,0:09:23.48,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,I sensed a magic unknown to me in the \Neast, and I saw its light fill the sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.90,0:09:25.90,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,It was world-class magic,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.90,0:09:30.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that which can alter the laws, fate, \Nand very existence of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.70,0:09:35.59,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,You are every bit the man I thought you were.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.17,0:09:39.34,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,If I hadn't met you, I never would've had the idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.87,0:09:41.85,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,You honor me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.85,0:09:43.11,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Incidentally,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.11,0:09:48.62,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,I also felt a powerful magic in \Nthe western sky, just recently.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.62,0:09:49.98,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,The western sky?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.32,0:09:55.74,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,It seems that one besides yourself \Nhas created a new form of magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.73,0:10:00.31,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,One of the adventurers, I assume.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.16,0:10:12.52,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,The western sky... Adventurers...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.03,0:10:14.10,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,That means
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.69,0:10:17.28,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,it would have to be in Minami, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.36,0:10:23.98,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,Akihabara, Shibuya, Minami, Susukino, Nakasu...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.39,0:10:27.89,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,Just as Akihabara has changed \Nsince our arrival in this world,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.89,0:10:29.84,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,the other cities have changed, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.81,0:10:35.73,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,Almost all the Shibuya adventurers \Nhave gone to Akihabara.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.80,0:10:42.07,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,Susukino never recovered from the \Ndeterioration it suffered after the Apocalypse.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.20,0:10:45.05,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,Ever since we saved Serara,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.05,0:10:48.51,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,we've sent several armies up to evacuate \Nanyone who wanted to leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.46,0:10:50.78,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,But there are still
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.78,0:10:55.09,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,over two hundred adventurers who continue \Nruling over the People of the Land.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.48,0:10:58.44,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,And Minami...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.35,0:11:03.61,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Yamato was once united as \Na single kingdom, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.61,0:11:04.74,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.74,0:11:06.30,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,After we last spoke, I studied up.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.12,0:11:11.48,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,As I recall, the Unified Westelande Empire...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.76,0:11:17.69,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,was swallowed up in the history of battles with \Ndemi-humans and the Luquenje, and died out.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.25,0:11:20.52,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,But the Cowen family is distantly related.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.80,0:11:21.77,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.77,0:11:24.76,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,As is the Holy Empire Westelande,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.76,0:11:27.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,which rules the country's western portion.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.38,0:11:32.04,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Within the territory is a city \Nof adventurers, Minami.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.74,0:11:36.31,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,And I'm told that a certain guild rules Minami.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.72,0:11:40.42,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Are you aware that the Demon Festival \Nof Suzaku Gate occurred in the west?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.09,0:11:42.74,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.74,0:11:46.64,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Though the eastern nobles don't \Nseem to have noticed yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.20,0:11:52.33,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,The Demon Festival of Suzaku Gate is similar \Nto the Return of the Goblin King.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.68,0:11:54.81,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,It's an event that occurs at set intervals.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.47,0:11:59.30,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,It appears the Izumo Knights \Nwere involved with it, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.50,0:12:06.31,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,The Demon Festival of Suzaku Gate...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.83,0:12:08.17,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,Hints of magic...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.21,0:12:11.07,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,Something is happening in Minami.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.68,0:12:13.66,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,I found you, Shiroe.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.88,0:12:17.96,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,Hide-and-seek is over.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.63,0:12:22.05,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,And so,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.55,0:12:25.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you'll be doing your share of the cleaning.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.64,0:12:28.18,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Sounds good to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.57,0:12:32.47,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Now you'll have the chance \Nto see why they call me
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.47,0:12:34.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the "Dish-washing Fox of High Society."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.94,0:12:36.85,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Dish-washing Fox?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.85,0:12:38.68,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,You couldn't make less sense if you tried.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.86,0:12:42.50,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Rudy, stop eating only meat, \Nand have some vegetables.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.57,0:12:45.79,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,No, there's no need for that...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.79,0:12:47.83,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Just eat it! Come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.83,0:12:49.59,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,No! Anything but that!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.59,0:12:50.20,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,Eat it!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.20,0:12:50.85,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.32,0:12:57.36,Default,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.36,0:12:58.61,Default,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,This song...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.04,0:13:02.35,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,This was {\i1}Elder Tale{\i0}'s theme song \Nwhen it was a game.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.83,0:13:05.34,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,It really is a nice song...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.34,0:13:08.56,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,But nobody's dancing.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.60,0:13:16.35,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,Both the People of the Land
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.08,0:13:20.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and the adventurers are too afraid \Nof each other to dance.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.28,0:13:26.48,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,For the sake of both, \Nsomeone should take the lead.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.08,0:13:30.83,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,I think you and I have that responsibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.53,0:13:32.76,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,Responsibility...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.17,0:13:50.46,Default - flashback,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Lenessia,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.73,0:13:57.98,Default - flashback,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,it was not Eastal that asked the \Nadventurers for help with the goblins.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.60,0:14:01.57,Default - flashback,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,It was you yourself, Lenessia.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.07,0:14:05.17,Default - flashback,L,0000,0000,0000,,Grandfather, that's...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.70,0:14:11.87,Default - flashback,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Eastal expresses its deepest thanks \Nto the adventurers of Akihabara,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.87,0:14:15.25,Default - flashback,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,but we have no obligation to do more.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.02,0:14:17.37,Default - flashback,L,0000,0000,0000,,In other words,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.23,0:14:24.00,Default - flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,you have no intention of offering them \Nreward money, or compensation money?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.00,0:14:26.49,Default - flashback,L,0000,0000,0000,,I must take responsibility myself?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.38,0:14:30.89,Default - flashback,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,My city, Maihama, will be establishing \Nan embassy in Akihabara,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.38,0:14:33.62,Default - flashback,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,and will be sending an ambassador.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.06,0:14:35.18,Default - flashback,L,0000,0000,0000,,You can't mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.98,0:14:38.98,Default - flashback,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,You spoke of showing respect.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.34,0:14:43.26,Default - flashback,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Thus, it is your responsibility \Nto stay with them,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.26,0:14:48.40,Default - flashback,,0000,0000,0000,,and to thank them whenever \Nthe opportunity arises.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.40,0:14:51.58,Default - flashback,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,No, it's simple courtesy, is it not?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.68,0:14:56.62,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,It comes with three meals and a nap.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.15,0:15:00.10,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,It comes with three meals and a nap.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.37,0:15:04.55,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,I believe you witnessed this yesterday,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.81,0:15:09.93,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,but adventurers aren't as concerned \Nwith formalities as nobles are.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.63,0:15:13.55,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,There are few tea parties or balls.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.54,0:15:17.03,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,That's the kind of town you'll be coming to.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.51,0:15:19.97,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,It should allow you to enjoy a \Nlife with three meals and a nap,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.97,0:15:22.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,never having to leave the house.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.22,0:15:24.13,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,Then...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.17,0:15:28.81,Default - italics,L,0000,0000,0000,,My old dream of enjoying three \Ndays of such laziness
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.81,0:15:30.95,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,that I don't even take a bath?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.32,0:15:35.20,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,Well, as long as it doesn't \Ngo much past three days.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.98,0:15:37.98,Default - italics,L,0000,0000,0000,,He read my mind again!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.01,0:15:41.46,Default - italics,L,0000,0000,0000,,No, no...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.46,0:15:43.58,Default - italics,L,0000,0000,0000,,I must not let my guard down.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.92,0:15:47.52,Default - italics,L,0000,0000,0000,,He is a monster that can read minds.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.52,0:15:48.34,Default - italics,L,0000,0000,0000,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.00,0:15:51.68,Default - italics,L,0000,0000,0000,,He's a mind-reading monster!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.09,0:15:54.24,Default,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,He's so wonderful!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.83,0:15:58.59,Default,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,Now I can finally return to \Nmy life of self-indulgence.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.59,0:15:59.76,Default,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,Right, Crusty?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.76,0:16:02.36,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.76,0:16:06.57,Default,Cr,0000,0000,0000,,You seem to have a habit \Nof ruining it for yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.14,0:16:08.09,Default,L,0000,0000,0000,,Ruining—
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.63,0:16:15.46,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,U-Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.46,0:16:18.16,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong, Serara?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.41,0:16:21.14,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,I... I'm...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.14,0:16:22.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Meow?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.42,0:16:27.59,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,I'm really grateful to you for \Nsaving me in Susukino.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.72,0:16:29.67,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.68,0:16:33.66,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,The Crescent Moon Alliance \Nhas done a lot for me,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.18,0:16:39.01,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,and I need to look after the new players, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.01,0:16:40.47,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.03,0:16:43.28,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,So I...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.64,0:16:44.95,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.98,0:16:48.30,Default - italics,Se,0000,0000,0000,,I want to be with Nyanta, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.18,0:16:51.52,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.51,0:16:54.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,can't stay in Log Horizon...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.57,0:16:55.77,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,Serara,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.30,0:17:00.33,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,you're such a good girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.00,0:17:04.92,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,Would you dance with me,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.93,0:17:07.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Serara?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.83,0:17:11.93,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.93,0:17:14.69,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,I'll go get something to drink.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.69,0:17:15.50,Default,T,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.48,0:17:19.26,Default - italics,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,Where is Shiroe?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.51,0:17:23.92,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Did you hear about how that \NShiroe guy tricked the princess?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.92,0:17:25.14,Default,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,I did...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.14,0:17:26.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He dragged her out to the battlefield,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.97,0:17:29.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and used her in negotiations \Nwith the People of the Land.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.87,0:17:32.04,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,You know, they call him a villain.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.04,0:17:35.28,Default,Girl,0000,0000,0000,,Who is he, anyway? What's he \Ndoing in the Round Table?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.28,0:17:36.28,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,I know guys like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.62,0:17:40.34,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,They skulk around the shadows, \Ntaking advantage of people's weaknesses.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.91,0:17:44.56,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,You aren't going, my lord?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.39,0:17:47.91,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,I think I'll pass.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.91,0:17:49.92,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Tonight, the star is Crusty.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.44,0:17:53.65,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,I'd just make things awkward and tire everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.90,0:17:57.79,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.18,0:17:59.70,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,It's nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.70,0:18:01.20,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.85,0:18:08.94,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you smirking, my lord?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.94,0:18:10.05,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not smirking.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.05,0:18:11.18,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,No, you were smirking!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.18,0:18:12.48,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,That isn't true.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.13,0:18:15.68,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,You were... You were smirking!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.05,0:18:20.28,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,You're acting kind of strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.03,0:18:26.80,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,This time, I hardly did anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.38,0:18:34.02,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Outside of battle, I think \NI only slowed you down.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.34,0:18:37.73,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,That's not true.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.61,0:18:43.02,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,You stayed with me the whole time, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.12,0:18:45.82,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Ever since we came here,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.39,0:18:49.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you've been my bodyguard, \Nand got me information.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.73,0:18:55.68,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,You heard what Regan said, and you shared \Nthe secret about our memories with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.02,0:18:59.32,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Even when I went to save Rundel Haus,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.78,0:19:02.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you were with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.39,0:19:07.70,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,I've only made it this far because of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.42,0:19:09.48,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,It's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.37,0:19:17.34,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,It's hard to express gratitude to someone...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.75,0:19:22.47,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Naotsugu!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.79,0:19:23.83,Default,M,0000,0000,0000,,Let's dance, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.83,0:19:25.47,Default,N,0000,0000,0000,,No, I don't really...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.47,0:19:26.56,Default,Sh,0000,0000,0000,,Marie...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.56,0:19:27.85,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,There, there...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.12,0:19:30.64,Default,R,0000,0000,0000,,Shall we dance, Miss Isuzu?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.40,0:19:36.30,Default,I,0000,0000,0000,,S-Sure...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.82,0:19:39.27,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,You're very good, Serara.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.27,0:19:40.86,Default,Se,0000,0000,0000,,Th-Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.02,0:19:42.94,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Would you like to dance?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.94,0:19:44.77,Default,H,0000,0000,0000,,I'd be honored.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.33,0:19:49.37,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Want to dance?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.63,0:19:52.81,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,No, my lord...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.81,0:19:55.49,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not good at dancing...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.92,0:19:57.88,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,You were practicing, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.26,0:20:00.13,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,No, that was, well...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.52,0:20:09.67,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,My lord...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.67,0:20:11.75,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,Don't laugh at me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.75,0:20:13.47,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a beginner, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.88,0:20:15.03,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,I won't laugh.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.07,0:20:17.57,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, my...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.57,0:20:20.57,Default,Ny,0000,0000,0000,,That is quite the dance, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.88,0:20:24.64,Default,A,0000,0000,0000,,My lord, is this a dance?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.64,0:20:26.06,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Don't laugh.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.20,0:20:30.51,SignD,S,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome, {\c&H9A55C7&}Princess {\c&HC4C996&}Lenessia!!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.20,0:20:30.51,SignA,S,0000,0000,0000,,Love {\c&HB1806D&}Lenessia
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.89,0:20:35.00,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,Several days later, Lenessia came to Akihabara.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.75,0:20:40.60,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,Rather than making a big deal of it,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.60,0:20:43.36,Default - italics,,0000,0000,0000,,I spread the news about the \Nlost memories as a rumor.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.39,0:20:47.77,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,But naturally, many were scared.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.46,0:20:51.14,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,But you only lose part of them, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.14,0:20:54.69,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,They say people who've died \Nten times have no problems.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.69,0:20:58.32,SignB,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Original Fishing Rods
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.69,0:20:58.32,SignF,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,All Kinds \Nof Lures!!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.95,0:20:58.32,Default - italics,S,0000,0000,0000,,But it didn't cause chaos.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.32,0:21:02.12,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,They say the Round Table knew, but hid it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.12,0:21:03.14,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.14,0:21:06.19,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Nah... I could see them doing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.19,0:21:08.11,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Especially that Shiroe guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.16,0:21:12.54,SignC,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Shiroe Memo #6\NBuilds, Skills, and Subclasses
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.54,0:21:16.28,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Minori?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.30,0:21:19.42,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,Is there still something you don't understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.37,0:21:22.46,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,No, I'm fine...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.98,0:21:23.77,Default,S,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.43,0:21:26.93,Default,Mi,0000,0000,0000,,U-Um...
